Sentencas: This work investigates the effects of alkali solution treatment on the electrochemical activity of the LSM/YSZ electrode for solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Effects of alkali solution treatment on the electrochemical activity of the strontium doped LaMnO3-based electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode treated by alkali solution exhibits an enhanced electrochemical activity, which is independent of alkali concentration and treatment time.
Titulo: Effects of alkali solution treatment on the electrochemical activity of the strontium doped LaMnO3-based electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Only surface-segregated Sr species is removed by alkali solution as verified by ICP-MS and XPS, which can be correlated to the enhancement of the electrode activity.
Titulo: Effects of alkali solution treatment on the electrochemical activity of the strontium doped LaMnO3-based electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode only treated by hot water shows a different impedance behavior from that for the case of alkali solution treatment, which can be correlated to the removal of Mn species.
Titulo: Effects of alkali solution treatment on the electrochemical activity of the strontium doped LaMnO3-based electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode treated by alkali solution can still be activated by cathodic polarization.
Titulo: Effects of alkali solution treatment on the electrochemical activity of the strontium doped LaMnO3-based electrode for solid oxide fuel cells
